Creates a new Array with the results of some operation. The Value its callback returns are used to from new array--returns a new array--foreach--does'nt creates a new array
syntax---arr.map(callbackFnx(val,index,array)
1) How to Use Map() with an example:
let nums=[2,3,4,5,6]
nums.map((val) => {
    console.log(val);
});

2) Creation of new array using Map():
let newArr = nums.map((val) => {
    return val;
});
console.log(newArr);
//FILTER METHOD
Creates a new array of elements that give true for a condition/filter
let arr=[1,2,3,4,5,6,7]
let evenArr = arr.filter( (val) => {
    return val % 2==0;
})
console.log(evenArr);
//REDUCE ARRAY METHOD
performs some operations and reduces the array to a single value
It returns that single value
const a=[1,2,3,4];
const output = a.reduce((prev, curr) => {
    return prev + curr;
})
console.log(output);

//largest number in an array
const a=[1,21,3,4];
const output = a.reduce((prev, curr) => {
    return prev>curr ? prev:curr;
})
console.log(output);
